The paper deals with image deblurring using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the physical image formation process and inverse rendering, which are related to computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of neural networks for self-supervised learning is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses both synthetic and real datasets, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
